de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.flow.coverage
Class DUCoverage

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.flow.coverage.DUCoverage

public class DUCoverage
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to keep track of the def-use (DefUseChain) coverage of a distinct method. When instantiated, maps which map instruction numbers to definition and uses are calculated. After doing so, recording coverage information is possible without consuming much execution time.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-08-28
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Method Detail

updateCoverage

public void updateCoverage(Method method,
                           int pc)
Update the coverage according to the instruction number.

In order to do so, check if there is any mapping for the given pc. If a mapping is found, update the definition coverage at the given index. Update the use coverage either if the definition required to form a def-use chain is already covered.

Parameters:
method - The method currently executed in the virtual machine.
pc - The current pc of the virtual machine.

revertCoverage

void revertCoverage(long number,
                    int coveredIndex,
                    boolean defOrUse)
Set the coverage of the definition or usage specified by the supplied index to false. If the number is higher then the point currently committed to, the total coverage will also be unset. This is needed since covering all chains might lead to the abortion of the execution. However, backtracking might take place without a solution saved. In such a case, coverage achieved would not be included in any solution, and yet has to be met again to fulfill the abortion criterion. This method has package visibility only. It is intended to be used by the restore() method of the DUCoverageTrailElement.

Parameters:
number - The number of the def-use coverage trail element.
coveredIndex - The index of the definition to unset.
defOrUse - Indicates whether the definition or the usage is unset. False means def, true means use.

getNumberOfCoveredDUChains

public int getNumberOfCoveredDUChains()
Get the number of covered def-use chains. Resetting definitions and usages while backtracking is taken into account. The number could however decrease, if currently some branches are covered that will be reseted later.

Returns:
The number of covered def-use chains.

getCoverage

public boolean[] getCoverage()
Get an array of boolean values indicating which def-use chains have been covered. A value of true indicates that the corresponding def-use chain is covered. Resetting definitions and usages while backtracking is taken into account. However, some covered chains could be set to be uncovered if no solution for the currently processed branch is found.

Returns:
An array of boolean values indicating which def-use chains have been covered.
